# Task Management System — Walkthrough

The Task Management System has been fully implemented, integrating **Laravel 12**, **Filament v3**, and **Livewire v3** to provide a dual-interface architecture for Administrators and Employees.

### Implementation Checklist
- ✅ **Laravel Project Setup:** Created project with `sqlite` and installed all required packages.
- ✅ **Database & Models:** Added `role` to Users and created the [Task](file:///c:/Users/hassa/OneDrive/Desktop/TaskMaster/app/Models/Task.php#9-47) model with relationships.
- ✅ **Authentication:** Configured Filament's session guards and built custom authentication endpoints for the Employee portal.
- ✅ **Admin Panel (Filament):** Implemented [UserResource](file:///c:/Users/hassa/OneDrive/Desktop/TaskMaster/app/Filament/Resources/UserResource.php#14-117) and [TaskResource](file:///c:/Users/hassa/OneDrive/Desktop/TaskMaster/app/Filament/Resources/TaskResource.php#14-142) for comprehensive CRUD operations, complete with employee-scoped assignment dropdowns. Created custom [StatsOverview](file:///c:/Users/hassa/OneDrive/Desktop/TaskMaster/app/Filament/Widgets/StatsOverviewWidget.php#10-41) and [OverdueTasks](file:///c:/Users/hassa/OneDrive/Desktop/TaskMaster/app/Filament/Widgets/OverdueTasksWidget.php#11-52) widgets for the admin dashboard.
- ✅ **Employee Frontend (Livewire):** Designed a responsive, Tailwind CSS-powered dashboard. Built the [TaskList](file:///c:/Users/hassa/OneDrive/Desktop/TaskMaster/app/Livewire/TaskList.php#8-35) Livewire component for real-time task status updates (Pending → In Progress → Completed) without page reloads.
- ✅ **Security:** Registered custom route middlewares ([EnsureUserIsAdmin](file:///c:/Users/hassa/OneDrive/Desktop/TaskMaster/app/Http/Middleware/EnsureUserIsAdmin.php#10-25), [EnsureUserIsEmployee](file:///c:/Users/hassa/OneDrive/Desktop/TaskMaster/app/Http/Middleware/EnsureUserIsEmployee.php#10-29)) to strictly enforce separation between `/admin` and employee routes.
- ✅ **Styling:** Setup a fully functional Tailwind CSS v4 pipeline via Laravel Vite. 

